title: Mariscal Nieto de Ilo
text:
Mariscal Nieto (<a href="Spanish%20language">Spanish</a> "mariscal" <a href="marshal">marshal</a>) is a <a href="Peru">Peru</a>vian <a href="football%20%28soccer%29">football</a> club, playing in the city of <a href="Ilo%2C%20Peru">Ilo</a>, <a href="Moquegua">Moquegua</a>, <a href="Peru">Peru</a>.
History.
Mariscal Nieto is of the clubs with greater tradition in the city of <a href="Ilo%2C%20Peru">Ilo</a>, <a href="Moquegua">Moquegua</a>. 
The club was the 1985 departamental champion and played in the <a href="1986%20Torneo%20Descentralizado">1986 Torneo Descentralizado</a> and <a href="1991%20Torneo%20Descentralizado">1991 Torneo Descentralizado</a>.
